            ">
           Fed chair faces Trump heat</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/trump-criticizes-powell-interest-rates.jpg" alt="Trump’s harsh criticism of Powell is mainly centered on the central bank not lowering interest rates quickly enough for his liking" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Trump’s harsh criticism of Powell is mainly centered on the Federal Reserve not lowering interest rates enough for his liking. Credits: Bloomberg
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
        President Trump met with Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell to discuss lowering <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-30-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-borrowing-expenses?source=website" target="_blank">borrowing expenses</a>. Trump considers the US interest percentage to be high, which is slowing the American economy by making it harder for people and businesses to borrow, invest, and grow. He added that the move puts the US at a significant economic disadvantage compared to China and other countries. He also hinted at the termination of Powell.  
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           Powell, however, reiterated that the Federal Reserve strives to stay independent and unbiased. The Federal Reserve also <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-30-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-announced?source=website" target="_blank">announced</a> that any adjustments to economic data will guide interest rates, focusing on indicators such as inflation and employment, rather than political considerations. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
         Trump has a history of criticizing Powell and has repeatedly questioned his competency. He <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-30-may-25-spotlight-h1-3-publicly-attacked?source=website" target="_blank">publicly attacked</a> Powell, calling him a “fool” for not cutting interest rates. Earlier, Trump even threatened to fire Powell and replace him with someone more aligned with his views. However, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-30-may-25-spotlight-h1-4-advisors-warned?source=website" target="_blank">advisors warned</a> that doing so could trigger market instability and undermine investor confidence in the Fed’s independence.</p>

          </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
